[SN]TITLE[SN]
Dumfries after-school group improvement ordered

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An after-school group in Dumfries has been told to make swift improvements to the care provided for children.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Care Inspectorate has issued a formal improvement notice to Lincluden After School Group, which lays out the areas which must be tackled.
They include ensuring a "competent, qualified and skilled person" can take charge in the manager's absence.
The group has also been told that children's "privacy and dignity" must be guaranteed at all times.
In order to do this they have must review their arrangements for changing children.
A spokesperson for the Care Inspectorate said: "We have clearly set out the areas which require swift improvement at Lincluden After School Group so that the care provided to children reaches a standard that they have a right to expect.
"We will inspect this service again soon to check on progress and to ensure that improvements have been made.
"If we are not satisfied that sufficient progress is being made quickly, we will not hesitate to take further action."
